reviews.text: Fabulous hidden gem in Happy Valley.  Fresh seafood.  Charming ambience.  Run don't walk!

We came here in a big group of 12 people, but it didnt affect their service quality. We tried their oysters, pork knuckle and a slow cooked beef brisket. Food was good. The beef brisket & ox tail were really a surprise

Delicious French oysters at HK$58 perfectly presented with excellent service. They also had plump, sweet clams from Russia that were amazing, prepared with white wine and butter with linguine at my request. Everyone else there were locals, so I would call this a hidden gem!
Fresh oyster, nice pasta, ham and dessert!
Ridiculously overpriced. Two glasses of  House wine, six oysters and mushroom pasta $129 US.
